"Wikipedia, eh? Must be accurate then!" - systemsmoke

I sense a little bit of ignorance here. Wikipedia is a non-profit organisation which allows it's users to publish their own pages. This means that it may not be 100% accurate but the pages are checked by staff who will post up a banner that comments on the information provided. There is also a sources list at the bottom of the page providing the research proof. There unfortunately isn't any for Season 9 but the proof is in the fact that there were two single double episodes (excuse the fact in normal circumstances this wouldn't make sense), meaning in theory, this would be episode 15, yes? So if if it's episode 14, you're counting one double episode is a double episode and one double episode as two single episodes meaning your logic must be off...
